OL,3,CWhat do Reeves' colossal Budget tax
OL,4,Cchanges mean for the economy?
OL,6,FThis Budget sees a record tax rise for
OL,7,Fmodern times - larger than those of
OL,8,FGeorge Osborne in 2010, Gordon Brown
OL,9,Fin 1997 and Norman Lamont in 1991.
OL,11,FPeople can make up their own minds
OL,12,Fabout whether Labour has broken
OL,13,Fpromises or not.
OL,15,FSpending plans laid out in the Labour
OL,16,Fmanifesto indicated a real terms rise
OL,17,Fin day-to-day spending of around 1%.
